<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Come come now.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:39 p.m. 1/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Come come now.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2111" TARGET=_self>Re: your loss of challenge is not our fault but your own.</A> (Trylix the mage)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Ok lets just say I don't KNOW what its like to die in this game. I never ever die. I don't get trained, I don't get rooted, I have dodged every SG in Oasis and jumped over every hole in Befallen. My pet has never chased a Froglock in Guk or lizard in Cazic Thule(those with pets will love this."Taunting attacker master", "WTF, wheres my pet", "/Pet follow me", "You no longer have a pet to command", "/g so can everyone here gate?"). Never been stoned by a basilisk in Rathe with a Giant Skeleton heading my way. And of course I have never died to a spectre twice while looking for my friends corpse in Oasis(Anyone else ever listed some memorable deaths? It is a fun reflection). The fact that I got to my level without dying is a credit to me and my gameplay. Some may have got there faster, they are better players or they play longer. Either way their time is less valuable. Now others that are not as good, or spend less time, can get levels alot easier. That is what I don't like. It was hard for me, I dealt without whining. Now some whiners are dying too much and the game is changing. It is BS. If you die cause someone rooted you in a train, THAT IS A DAMN SHAME, but you die sometimes(besides, if you are running with a train you already screwed up and deserve to die). BE MORE CAREFUL.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
